Look forward to working together to strengthen India-Australia Comprehensive Strategic Partnership and cooperation in the Indo-Pacific.","photos":null,"videos":null}
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
Increasing cancer survival rates. Controlling chronic pain. Understanding what causes debilitating genetic conditions.

600 researchers will be hard at work to make all that possible, right here in Adelaide.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
Peter Dutton was never serious about climate change. 

And he still won’t tell the Australian people where he plans to put his nuclear reactors - or how much they will cost.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description: We're wiping 3 billion in student debt, for more than 3 million Australians.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
Local sport is at the heart of our communities. Everyone pitches in to make it possible for these youngsters to dream of careers in sport.

That’s why we’re pitching in too, helping make these upgrades possible.

Doing our part to make this sporting community even stronger.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
The gender pay gap is at an all-time low. 
 
Business investment is up. 
 
Annual growth in real wages is back. 

There’s more to do, and I’ve never been more optimistic about the opportunities ahead for Australia.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
After their son Daniel was tragically taken from them, Bruce and Denise Morcombe channelled their pain into protecting children.

For almost 20 years, they've been educating children on staying safe, helping victims of crime and supporting families of missing persons.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
We've just had a breakthrough.

Tunnel boring machines Penny and Eileen have finished their not-so-boring work connecting the Metro to Western Sydney Airport.

I couldn’t miss the chance to thank Penny, Eileen and the more than 10,000 workers who’ve got us to this point.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
Australia strongly supports President Biden’s ceasefire proposal announced this week.

Here at home we must foster the unity and cohesion and diversity that has always been our nation’s greatest strength.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
While so many Australians were defending us in the Pacific, 3,300 fought in Europe alongside our partners in the US, UK, France, Canada and New Zealand.

Like Flight-Sergeant Fred Wood of Adelaide, pictured here after the landing with a French Gendarme in a Normandy village.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
This project will move 15,500 people across Sydney every hour. 

It’s creating jobs now and building for the future. That’s what we’re all about.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
Great to speak with @narendramodi today to congratulate him on his election victory. 

Australia and India are close friends, with strong strategic, economic and cultural ties. We look forward to growing our partnership in 2024 and beyond. 🇦🇺🇮🇳
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
She's done that as a Councillor, as a lawyer, and I know that's what she will do in Parliament.

Australians are under pressure, and our team is determined to do something about it.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
We are working every day to deliver for Australia.

We’re building the clean energy infrastructure to power a future made here in Australia. 

We are training more tradies and wiping $3b in student debt. 
 
Unemployment remains at near 50 year lows.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
Meet Claire Clutterham. She’s been an advocate for South Australians all her life, and I’ve asked her to stand as Labor’s candidate for Sturt.

“If you have the capacity to do it, you should speak up and advocate for others," Claire says.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
Union members fought for these reforms. Together, we’ve been able to get them done.

And tonight’s ACTU Congress was a chance to thank members for their hard work.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
We're taking action on climate change and creating secure jobs for Australians.

Peter Dutton wants to take Australia backwards, walking away from cleaner and cheaper energy.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
Today we give our thanks to all who stood for liberty – and we remember all who fell. 

D-Day was an unprecedented feat of collective willpower and daring. It was the free world’s decisive reply to the poison of Nazi tyranny.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description: We’re giving your household $300 off power bills from July 1.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
It means we can freeze the cost of PBS medicines for the next 12 months.

And make sure Australians can get the healthcare they need without worrying about the cost.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description: We've just introduced a bill to keep women safe from harmful deepfakes. Sharing explicit deepfake material without consent is abuse. We're making it a crime.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
Peter Dutton has a lot of questions to answer about nuclear.

It's time for him to say which Australian towns and cities he wants nuclear reactors to be built in.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
We supported a pay rise for Australia’s lowest paid workers.

And today's 3.75% increase to award wages delivers on that.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
Today I welcomed Nauru President David Adeang to Parliament. We had good discussions about our shared priorities and vision for Australia-Nauru relations.

Our countries have an enduring bond and a shared commitment to building a peaceful, stable and prosperous region. 🇦🇺🇳🇷
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
We're also making sure Australians keep more of what they earn with our tax cuts for every Australian taxpayer.

We know Australians are under pressure and we’re determined to do something about it.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
We’ll always stand up for Australian workers. I’m so proud of what we’ve already delivered.

More secure jobs. Better pay. Stronger rights for casual and gig workers. Paid family and domestic violence leave. And so much more.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description: Last month was all about helping Australians under pressure.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
What do these beautiful parts of Australia have in common?

They’re at risk of a nuclear reactor in their backyard under Peter Dutton.

Australians have waited 673 days for details on Peter Dutton's nuclear plan. He still won't say what cities and towns he'll put under threat.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
Wonderful to celebrate Italian National Day with @Coasitsydney tonight, this year raising funds for a dedicated dementia service for the Italian community. 

Buona festa della repubblica! 🇦🇺🇮🇹
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
Our goal of building 1.2 million homes is ambitious but achievable.  

All Governments need to work with industry to cut red tape, train more tradies, and build more homes. 

So we can see more housing projects like this.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description: Mate against mate. State against state. Backing the @nswblues in tonight's Origin opener.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description: After our @AussieDiamonds won last year's tournament, participation in netball is at an all time high. And there's quite a few fans here in Parliament.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
Check out these before and after photos ➡️ ➡️ 

A few months ago, this house was in disrepair. So we partnered with the NSW Government to fix it up, along with hundreds of others. 

A family will be moving in soon.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description: 2.6 million Australians will get a pay rise from 1 July.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description: I know you're busy, so I wanted to come on here and give you a quick rundown on how we’re helping with the cost of living.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
We’re training more tradies, cutting red tape, supporting construction and working with governments at every level.

I spoke with the Property Council of Australia about the Federal Government’s investment of $32 billion in new housing initiatives.
biography: Prime Minister of Australia. Member for Grayndler. Authorised by Anthony Albanese, ALP, Canberra.

name: Anthony Albanese
description:
Australian wine employs more than 160,000 people.

And now the industry is set for more success with China’s removal of duties on Australian wine.

name: sia
description: Had to take a medication that made me put on a lot of weight that I just can’t shift with exercise or thyroid meds so I went in for lipo today. Please know that I am so lucky to have the resources to change the way I look and that when you see me looking crazy foxy again (🤪)that I want you to know it did not come from diet and exercise. I want to be truthful about all of my procedures so I don’t contribute to the system that tells us we aren’t enough. I am insecure like most people and being in the public eye gives me anxiety, so I’ve made the choice to alter my appearance for my own confidence issues. Pray for me please! 🙏 I love you, keep going!

VIC – Over 4,000

Why would Peter Dutton cut housing in the middle of a housing crisis?

name: Clare O'Neil MP
description:
Labor’s Home of Your Own Plan means lower deposits and smaller mortgages for hundreds of thousands of first home buyers over the next few years, getting you into a home of your own, sooner.

Under Labor, we’re making it easier to buy, better to rent, and we’re building more homes.
biography: MP for Hotham. Minister for Housing and Minister for Homelessness. Authorised by C.O'Neil, ALP, Oakleigh

name: Clare O'Neil MP
description:
I’ve got first hand experience of the Coalition saying one thing before the election, and doing the complete opposite after.

The day before the 2013 election, Tony Abbott promised there would be no cuts to education. And we all saw what happened next—they ripped $30 billion out of public schools.

So when they say they back Labor’s investments to Medicare - take it with a very large pinch of salt.

name: Clare O'Neil MP
description:
Labor is helping some of Australia’s most vulnerable people secure their most fundamental need—a roof over their heads.

That’s why we’re opening a $1 billion fund for crisis accommodation for women and children fleeing domestic violence and we’re boosting our funding of homelessness groups so we can continue our work to reduce homelessness.

There is more work to do, but these announcements will make a real difference to women and children escaping family and domestic violence, and people at risk of homelessness.

name: Clare O'Neil MP
description:
New reporting today has revealed the 183 social and affordable housing projects across the country that will be bulldozed if Peter Dutton is elected. That’s over 13,000 homes!

There’s a clear choice on housing: Between a Labor Party that's building 55,000 social and affordable homes, or a Coalition that did nothing on housing for a decade and now wants to cut $19 billion from the housing budget.
biography: MP for Hotham. Minister for Housing and Minister for Homelessness. Authorised by C.O'Neil, ALP, Oakleigh

name: Clare O'Neil MP
description:
We're building 55,000 social and affordable homes across the country, including right here in Melbourne’s south east.

In a couple of months, these social  homes in Holt will be complete, with tenants moving in. It was wonderful to check on the site’s progress with local member Cassandra Fernando. I’m so looking forward to coming back when it’s all done.

We've launched the largest housing construction project in Australian history, directly investing in new homes like these—just as we used to.

Labor is tackling the housing crisis from every angle with our Home of Your Own Plan. We’re making it easier to buy, better to rent, and building more homes.
biography: MP for Hotham. Minister for Housing and Minister for Homelessness. Authorised by C.O'Neil, ALP, Oakleigh

name: Clare O'Neil MP
description:
ICYMI: We're opening 50 more free Medicare Urgent Care Clinics right across Australia.

4 in 5 Australians will live within a 20-minute drive from a Medicare Urgent Care Clinic under Labor.
biography: MP for Hotham. Minister for Housing and Minister for Homelessness. Authorised by C.O'Neil, ALP, Oakleigh

name: Clare O'Neil MP
description: 11/ If you want to know how Peter Dutton and the Liberals view housing, just look at their record of consistently voting AGAINST improving housing affordability
biography: MP for Hotham. Minister for Housing and Minister for Homelessness. Authorised by C.O'Neil, ALP, Oakleigh

name: Clare O'Neil MP
description:
Breaking news and breaking ground 📷

Construction  has begun in Arncliffe, Sydney, on 231 new social homes, funded by  Labor’s Housing Australia Future Fund. Soon, these homes will be  available for seniors and priority social and affordable housing  applicants. They’re also conveniently located near public transport and  amenities.

It was fantastic to tour the site with Ash Ambihaipahar, Labor’s incredible candidate for Barton, in her local community.

Across  the country, we’re building 55,000 social and affordable homes—six  times more than the former government delivered in its entire time in  office.

We’re tackling the  housing crisis from every angle with Labor's Home of Your Own  plan—making it easier to buy, better to rent, and building more homes.
biography: MP for Hotham. Minister for Housing and Minister for Homelessness. Authorised by C.O'Neil, ALP, Oakleigh

name: Clare O'Neil MP
description:
Half a million homes have been built since Labor came into office. 

There's more work to do and that's why we’ve set a big target to build 1.2 million homes over 5 years, which includes 55,000 new social and affordable homes funded by the Albanese Government. 

That’s 6x more than the Libs funded in their decade in office. A thread 🧵
biography: MP for Hotham. Minister for Housing and Minister for Homelessness. Authorised by C.O'Neil, ALP, Oakleigh

description:

This is the rate relief Australians need and deserve.

It’s a demonstration of the substantial and sustained progress we’ve made on inflation together.

It

name: Clare O'Neil MP
description:
12/ Whatever juvenile politics they try to play, there’s no contest here. Our government is the boldest and most ambitious Australian Government on housing since the post-war period. 

The Liberals did nothing for nine years and for most of that period, were so checked out they didn’t even have a housing minister. 

And, their only plan for housing is to cut $19b out of our housing budget - the opposite of what’s needed, given the housing challenge facing the country.
biography: MP for Hotham. Minister for Housing and Minister for Homelessness. Authorised by C.O'Neil, ALP, Oakleigh

name: Clare O'Neil MP
description:
We're providing $100 million for crisis and transitional accommodation across Australia for women and children impacted by family violence or at risk of homelessness.

42 organisations nationwide will receive a share of the $100 million to build new crisis and emergency accommodation.

These projects will save lives—this cannot be overstated. They will help thousands of women and children escape domestic violence and homelessness.

The Albanese Government is building more homes to make housing more affordable and protect our most vulnerable.

name: Clare O'Neil MP
description:
We don't want young people in this country to have to choose between furthering your education and getting into a home of your own.

That's why we’re working with the regulators to ensure Australians with student debt are treated fairly when it comes to taking out a mortgage. 

These are common-sense changes that will have a significant impact.

Whether it's expanding the number of low-deposit options, wiping student debt by 20% -- we're focussed on getting young Australians into a home of your own.
biography: MP for Hotham. Minister for Housing and Minister for Homelessness. Authorised by C.O'Neil, ALP, Oakleigh

description:

Our doctors and nurses work so incredibly hard to keep Australians healthy. 

And our changes will mean all you'll need to see them is your Medicare card – not your credit card. 

Saving families hundreds of dollars every year.

description:
Breaking news: Labor's helped more than 200,000 Australians get into a home of their own through with lower deposits thanks to our expanded Home Guarantee Scheme.

People are doing it tough -- especially on housing -- but we're making good progress and there's lots more to do.

There’s still places this financial year for the Home Guarantee Scheme.

description:
Labor holds the simple belief that ordinary Australians should be able to buy a home of their own.

That's where our Help to Buy scheme comes in.

We're making it easier for you to get into your own home with a smaller mortgage and smaller deposit.

The scheme will come online in the middle of this year and we'll have more updates soon. You can learn more here: https://t.co/arrDfKCquy
biography: MP for Hotham. Minister for Housing and Minister for Homelessness. Authorised by C.O'Neil, ALP, Oakleigh

description:

So more Australians can see the doctor for free.
biography: MP for Hotham. Minister for Housing and Minister for Homelessness. Authorised by C.O'Neil, ALP, Oakleigh

name: Clare O'Neil MP
description:
Roads. Sewage. Water.

These may not be the first things people think about when building homes, but they’re essential to creating the housing Australia needs.

That’s why the Albanese Labor Government is investing over $180 million in critical infrastructure to unlock 25,000 homes across New South Wales.

And there’s more to come.

Our government is starting the biggest home-building program in Australian history to get more people get into their own home.

Labor's building Australia's future and helping to build your future with a home of your own.

description:
The attack on the Adass Israel synagogue in Ripponlea is an abhorrent act of anti-Semitism and I unequivocally condemn it. 

Built by Holocaust survivors who came to Australia to build a new life, this synagogue provided a refuge of peace, safety and prayer to the Jewish community in my part of Melbourne and to constituents in my own electorate of Hotham. 

This attack goes against everything that we stand for here in Melbourne and across Australia at large, and my thoughts and solidarity are with the Jewish community affected during this awful time.

name: Clare O'Neil MP
description:
BREAKING:

We’ve just passed our Build to Rent legislation which paves the way for the construction of 80,000 new homes to rent.

These 80,000 rental properties will have a minimum of 5-year leases and 10% of these homes will provide subsidised rent for low- and moderate-income  earners.

And these Build to Rent projects will be prevented from using no fault evictions.

That's security and stability for 80,000 households. 

We’re  working across Government and with states and territories to help build  more homes, making it easier for Australians to rent and buy.
biography: MP for Hotham. Minister for Housing and Minister for Homelessness. Authorised by C.O'Neil, ALP, Oakleigh

description:

This partnership  is expected to unlock up to $3 billion in new investment in social housing across Australia, creating thousands of new construction jobs. 

With  Australians doing it tough, this partnership will support thousands of  Australians to get into social housing, helping reduce homelessness and  taking pressure off rents. 

We're  building more homes for renters, homes for first-home buyers, homes for the most vulnerable in our community, because the more homes we build,  the more affordable housing becomes.
biography: MP for Hotham. Minister for Housing and Minister for Homelessness. Authorised by C.O'Neil, ALP, Oakleigh

From NIMBY to YIMBY and now, YIGBY -- “yes in God’s backyard”

Yes to more homes for those in need, yes to more homes for renters, yes to more homes for everyone.

Two pieces of the puzzle are before the Senate this week – two pieces which have been blocked and delayed by Peter Dutton and the Greens.

We’re partnering with the Roger Cook Labor Government to deliver one of the single biggest boosts to affordable housing housing in WA’s history.

And these new homes will be built near public transport.

In this first round, we’re building 14 developments in Ellenbrook, Byford, Brabham, Redcliffe, Wellard, Woodbridge, Banksia Grove, Rivervale, White Gum Valley, Subiaco East, Albany, Dallyellup, Golden Bay and Treeby – delivering nearly 1100 new homes.

Housing changes lives, and we’re determined to get more homes built.

We won’t stop working to make sure every Australian has the security and safety of a roof over their head.

The Albanese Government’s Help to Buy scheme has passed parliament.

Labor holds the simple belief that ordinary Australians should own their own home, and today that got a little easier.

While people are still doing it very tough, today is a good day for homeownership.

Thousands of Australians – educators, carers, cleaners, nurses – who have been locked out of the housing market, will have a shot at owning their own home.

This scheme will make it easier for people on low and middle incomes to buy a home of their own with a smaller mortgage and smaller deposit.

That's security and stability for 80,000 households.

And 10% of these homes will provide subsidised rent for low- and moderate-income earners.

This is what our Build to Rent bill will deliver if it passes Parliament this week.

We've been working hard with crossbenchers and key stakeholders to make sure we're passing the best bill possible and I want to thank them for working so constructively with our government.

It was a pleasure to join @DavidPocock, @spenderallegra, @KyleaTink, Mike Zorbas from the @PropertyCouncil, Wendy Hayhurst from @CHIA_News, and John Engeler from @NationalShelter to announce some of the good faith work we've been doing together to deliver these new rental homes for Australians.

Michael Sukkar has just announced the Liberals would not match Labor's ambitious housing target. He has also threatened to slash housing funding for States and Territories. 

They've already committed to slashing the $10 billion Housing Australia Future Fund for more social and affordable housing.

All the Liberals have to offer is cuts to housing funding - after a decade where their inaction made the problem worse. 

And the Greens say the right things but then when it comes time to make a difference, play politics instead of making progress. 

Labor is the only party with a real plan for housing. It’s not one simple answer - because there isn’t one simple answer. It’s serious and sustained action, to build more homes, better protect renters and help more Australians into home ownership.

It’s not good enough and the Greens need to be accountable for that.

The Australian Government is

It’s just part of our cyber security strategy that will help make Australia a word leader in cyber security by 2030.

And we need to capture lessons learned from cyber attacks, so that we can strengthen our national defences and stay ahead of the threat.
biography: MP for Hotham. Minister for Housing and Minister for Homelessness. Authorised by C.O'Neil, ALP, Oakleigh

description: And we’ll continue to work with our international partners to drive the Counter Ransomware Initiative and break the global ransomware business model.
biography: MP for Hotham. Minister for Housing and Minister for Homelessness. Authorised by C.O'Neil, ALP, Oakleigh

description:

biography: MP for Hotham. Minister for Housing and Minister for Homelessness. Authorised by C.O'Neil, ALP, Oakleigh

That’s why the Albanese Government is taking action to strengthen the cyber security of the telecommunication sector.

description:

Operations have resumed at the company's ports across Australia at 9 AM today following successful tests of key systems overnight.

DP World Australia expects that approximately 5,000 containers will move out of the four Australian terminals today.
biography: MP for Hotham. Minister for Housing and Minister for Homelessness. Authorised by C.O'Neil, ALP, Oakleigh

description:

biography: MP for Hotham. Minister for Housing and Minister for Homelessness. Authorised by C.O'Neil, ALP, Oakleigh

description: We’re also  going to share lessons learned from these exercises with the broader  community.  Cyber attacks are not going away, and we need to make sure our essential services are prepared and can bounce back quickly.

We're adding more medicines to the PBS so Australians can get the treatment they need, without cost getting in the way.

Look after one another, be kind, and stay safe.

Every year, around 227,000 tonnes of clothing is sent to landfill in Australia.

The fashion industry is responsible for 10 per cent of humanity’s carbon emissions – more carbon than international flights and maritime shipping combined.
 
We need to cut fashion waste.

An activist and leader, he campaigned tirelessly against corruption. His opposition to Putin’s cruel regime has brought hope to many in his country and inspired the world.

The Russian Government should answer for his treatment and death.

The last minute cancellation this year is terrible.

Every death in this conflict is a tragedy. 

More than a million people have fled to seek safety in Rafah, including more than 600,000 children. 

An attack on Rafah would be unjustifiable.

16 years ago today, people gathered in the rain in Redfern in my electorate to watch Kevin Rudd deliver the apology to the Stolen Generations. 

That day in parliament was sad and beautiful. 

Saying sorry is important and we have to match it with action. There is still a lot of work to do.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
You may remember that before Christmas I let you know about an emergency decision I made to save the Red Handfish. I wanted to give you an update about how it’s going.

The Red Handfish is critically endangered. There are just 50 - 100 left in the wild. 

So, based on expert advice, we removed 25 fish and housed them at breeding facilities in Tasmania during the expected summer marine heatwaves.

All are doing well. We’re hoping to return them back to their home before winter.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
Dr Lowitja O’Donoghue was a fearless and tireless advocate for Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Australians. 

Her determination to make the world a fairer place for First Nations people made her one of the most formidable and influential leaders our country has seen.

The first woman to be a regional director of an Australian federal department, founding Chairperson of the National Aboriginal Conference and the first Aboriginal woman to be made a Member of the Order of Australia in 1997. 

Named Australian of the Year in 1984, she received many national and international accolades and awards in recognition of her work and became a National Living treasure in 1998.

She will be missed. Rest in strength and peace.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

Medicare is 40 today. 10 years ago I joined Bob Hawke to celebrate Medicare’s 30th. 

Bob isn’t with us today, but his vision of healthcare in Australia is. The cheapest, simplest, and fairest healthcare system. Here’s to Bob, and here’s to Medicare.

Everyone deserves to be safe.

Turning the tide on nature repair will take a global effort. That’s why we’re bringing together Governments, private sector, environmentalists and First Nations groups to work together for a nature positive future.

This guy is one of the healthy babies born in Dhilba Guuranda-Innes National Park where the re-introduced population is booming. Best comeback story ever.

An army of volunteers have taken to the Adelaide coastline as part of a seagrass rehabilitation program. This work is restoring our marine ecosystems so they can store carbon from the atmosphere.

We’ve provided $9.5 million to restore Australia’s coastal ecosystems through projects like this.
 
Combatting climate change and better protecting our marine life for our kids and grandkids. Fantastic.

If you’re someone who vapes, perhaps this is your sign to make quitting vaping your New Year’s resolution.

The red handfish lives in Tasmania’s Derwent River. There are only about 50-100 of them left in the wild. 

Experts have warned that the handfish may not survive this summer’s expected marine heatwaves. To give them a better chance, I’ve approved an emergency intervention under environment law to move the 25 to breeding facilities in Tasmania.

✅ Passed legislation to establish the world’s first Nature Repair Market, to boost investment in nature and prevent greenwashing. 

✅ Updated the water trigger in our environment law to cover unconventional gas projects. 

✅ Rescued the Murray-Darling Basin Plan, to deliver an extra 180,000 Olympic swimming pools of water for the environment.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
Nature repair is a huge job and we know that many businesses are keen to play a role, but they want to be sure that they are having an impact.

Our new Nature Finance Council will strengthen our efforts to protect more of what’s precious and repair more of what’s damaged. I’m pleased Dr Ken Henry is bringing his considerable experience and passion to this role, to help develop new ideas and shape the future of nature repair.

Working alongside industry, scientists, environmental organisations and First Nations groups we will turn the tide from nature destruction to nature repair, ensuring that investments are really making a difference.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
Peta Murphy was one of a kind. Dedicated, determined, passionate, smart, funny and strong. 

A lot of people know about Peta’s advocacy for  breast cancer treatment. Not so many know that many of Labor’s reforms to reduce the gender pay gap started with her. 

She fought off the Liberals plan to make domestic violence survivors drain their Super before getting government support.

She was proud to represent an electorate named for Louisa Dunkley - a trade unionist and a feminist. 

Peta was a wonderful representative for a community she loved passionately and fought for fiercely. 

Sending love to all who loved her. What a huge loss, and how lucky we all were to be her comrades.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

description: This was my favourite part of last night’s 730 interview with @tanya_plibersek, who delivered more environmental water in her first nine months as Water Minister than the Liberals did in their nine years. #auspol
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
I don’t want Australians to wake up to a dead river one day and know that their Parliament could’ve done something, but didn’t. 

When I visited the Basin in 2022 a local showed me this photo of the river in their town when it ran dry.  

The Senate needs to pass this Bill before the end of the year. Communities and the environment can’t afford for us not to.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: Behind the scenes on @abc730 last night. Thanks for having me to chat about our Bill to rescue the Murray-Darling Basin Plan.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
Thank you @sarahinthesen8 for your collaboration to strengthen this important legislation. 

We’ll keep having conversations with all parties who want to deliver this bill - we must get this done.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: Read more about this important appointment here:
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: In case you missed the news: here’s just one way we’re investing to protect our precious Great Barrier Reef.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
This is Ricky Archer.

This week he became our first ever First Nations Director of National Parks. 

We know that when we lean on First Nations expertise and work together with Traditional Owners, we better protect our environment and we give visitors a better understanding of what makes our precious places special.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
Debate on our bill to rescue the Murray-Darling Basin Plan has just started in the Senate.

After a decade of sabotage by the Liberals and Nationals, it's critical we deliver this plan - to protect threatened plants and animals, food production, and the drinking water for more than 3 million Australians.

Today, we've announced we've reached an agreement with the Greens to strengthen our legislation and ensure they support it in the Senate.

If the bill doesn't pass this year, the plan collapses.

With another drought around the corner, our communities and our environment can't afford this.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
It’s a big day for a big weir. The Rookwood Weir is the largest built in Australia since World War 2 - and it’s now complete. 

The weir will hold the same amount of water as 34,400 Olympic swimming pools. 

As well as boosting water security, the Rookwood Weir features a fish lock and turtle passage that will support local species.

A win for nature, win for jobs and a win for water security in Central Queensland.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
They make not look pretty - but these jars are pretty important. In Australia we print 10.6 billion receipts a year, many of which can’t be recycled and are covered in toxic chemicals. 

These jars are showing us how those receipts breakdown over time and pollute our environment. 

Great to see UTS and industry working together and finding solutions to tackle this waste.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: You can find out more here:
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
As summer approaches, we’re listening to the experts to make sure we’re working to protect our precious Great Barrier Reef. 

That’s why we’re investing $200 million to improve water quality - supporting projects that protect the gullies, creeks and riverbanks that flow into the reef.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: Another renewables project ticked off - powering 45,000 NSW homes. This is what action on climate change looks like.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: Some big news! Thanks to Labor’s investment, and Australia’s fantastic researchers, we’re on track to eliminate cervical cancer. Proud to be part of a goverment that takes women’s health seriously.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: No one wants to imagine a future without koalas. That’s why we’re investing $12.4 Million to fund koala health projects across Queensland - so koalas like Brandy can get the care they need when disaster strikes.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: You can read more here:
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
When we value First Nations expertise, when we empower First Nations communities on the ground, we get better outcomes. 

Yesterday at the 25th anniversary celebration of Indigenous Protected Areas, we announced $160.5 million to make sure our IPAs can continue to protect and care for our environment for years to come.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
The Great Barrier Reef is one the most beautiful places on Earth. We want to better protect it for our kids and grandkids.

We know one of the most immediate threats to health of Reef is unsustainable fishing practices. Destructive gillnet fishing causes damage throughout the Reef, and injures and kills threatened dugongs, turtles, dolphins and protected shark species.

Good to see the Queensland Government announce next steps to support industry as we phase out gillnets on the Great Barrier Reef World Heritage Area by mid-2027.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: 6 years ago today Australia said Yes to love.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: First Nations Heritage Grants are open now:
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: We’re lucky to have so many precious places as part of our heritage. We’re investing $5.5 million to better recognise and protect the Indigenous heritage of these places.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: The last government said low wages were a ‘deliberate design feature of their economic architecture’. Our government promised to get wages growing and we are.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: The people you run into at Parliament House @Tonaaayy_
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: A sustainable, healthy river system for communities, industry, farmers, First Nations and the environment.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
The Australian Sea Lion is found nowhere else in the world and is Australia’s most endangered seal. 

Communities in South Australia know how important it is to protect this precious species.

Thats why we’ve announced almost half a million dollars towards research and recovery of these unique animals.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
Farmers, First Nations leaders, and community members have travelled to Canberra from across the Murray-Darling Basin with a clear message: we need to rescue the Murray-Darling Basin Plan. 

With another drought around the corner, we can’t afford any more delay. The parliament needs to pass our bill.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
We've boosted our recycling capacity by an extra 1.3 million tonnes per year.

This is great for the environment, but it's also great for the economy. For every job in landfill, there are three jobs in recycling - we’re creating more than 3000 jobs in recycling.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
Today the parliament will mark the fifth anniversary of the National Apology to Victims and Survivors of Institutional Child Sexual Abuse. 

Thinking of everyone who shared their stories or spoke up for others. Harrowing, difficult stories, powerfully shared to demand justice.  

The apology was an important first step. We’re committed to making sure it’s met with action.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
On the 11th hour on the 11th day of the 11th month, we remember them.

Lest we forget.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
We’ve doubled the rate of approvals of renewables projects, like this one in Queensland. 

Ten years of delay and denial is over and we’re working hard to help Australia become a renewable energy superpower.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
In the last 150 years, native fish populations have declined by more than 90 per cent. We have to turn this around before it’s too late.

When I was in Menindee last month I heard how important a better fish passage would be to help stop fish deaths - like the large-scale ones we’ve seen in recent years. So we’re investing $2.3 million to help deliver one.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
We’re investing $11.6 million in koala health projects across QLD, like a new infectious disease ward for koalas and developing a vaccine to fight koala disease. These projects will play a crucial role in protecting and conserving this beloved animal.

Read more here: https://t.co/DqmfDPICiX
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
Good news today from NSW Minister @RoseBJackson 

The NSW gov has begun immediate work to reduce the risk of more fish deaths occurring this summer. 

Supported by $2.3m from @tanya_plibersek to develop a business case for the construction of permanent fish passage at Menindee
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
It’s going to be another hot and dry summer. We're giving our wildlife a better chance during the next bushfire season. 

That’s why we’re investing $13.2 million to help local organisations and farmers prepare and protect native plants and animals against natural disasters.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
Plastic pollution is a global problem, it requires a global solution. 

That’s why we’re backing an international treaty to end plastic pollution - with clear, binding targets to help us get there. 

Here’s the latest statement from the group of countries Australia is working with as we head into another round of negotiations in Kenya soon. 

https://t.co/ZmIHWNHbwQ
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
With two icons - @TerriIrwin and Brandy the koala.

Brandy is such a special part of the @AustraliaZoo family that she walked down the aisle at @BindiIrwin 's wedding!
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: Couldn’t love you more, Anna.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: Read my speech to WA Labor conference here:
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
With Peter Dutton, it’s never a constructive opposition. It’s never a search for collaboration  or compromise in the national interest.

It’s always the poisonous politics of no.

Peter Dutton is not a man who can deliver, he can only sabotage.

We can’t let this style of politics take over. And that applies across the board, to all parties.

Don’t follow Peter Dutton’s lead.

Don’t team up with him in parliament, don’t choose politics over people.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
Protecting the environment is a global challenge. 

Last week, I signed a new agreement with the United States Environmental Protection Agency to work together to better protect the environment by sharing data, discussing common issues, and discuss strengthening environmental laws. 

All of this resulting in better environmental decisions and enforcement.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: We’re building renewables projects right across Australia. This solar farm we’ve ticked off will be built alongside a new battery to help get cheaper, cleaner power to 86,000 South Australian homes.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: Some big news. We’ve made the largest investment ever in bulk billing and it kicks in today - helping more than 11 million people see a doctor with just their Medicare card.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
For more than 2.5 years, 20 trucks have carted water each day into the community of Mount Morgan in Queensland.

We want to make sure communities across Australia have reliable and secure water. That’s why today we’ve announced another $26.5 million to fund the Mount Morgan pipeline to bring an end to water carting and ensure the sustainability and liveability of the town.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
We’ve ticked off this solar project in regional NSW. Powering almost 50,000 homes - that’s more than the population of Dubbo. 

Even better - we’ve got more than 100 renewable energy projects like this one in the pipeline.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
You may remember earlier this year I announced a voluntary water purchasing open tender to complete one part of the Murray-Darling Basin Plan.

The good news is we received around 250 tender responses - totalling more than double the amount of water as the tender called for.

This is a fantastic sign that voluntary water purchase is a necessary and feasible tool to help meet the targets of the Murray-Darling Basin Plan.

With the next drought around the corner, we're focused on delivering the Plan to ensure a healthy river system for the communities, industries, and environment that rely on it.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: Such sad and unexpected news about Helena Carr. Lively, intelligent, fiercely loyal, and great company. She will be very dearly missed.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
Today, we kick off a further round of more detailed consultation on our new nature laws.

We’re talking about over 1,000 pages of complex laws - we are determined to get this right. 

Experts from more than 30 groups, including environment, business, and industry, will be able carefully examine the detail to make sure the laws will be as effective as possible.  

There will also be a series of public information sessions and an opportunity for the public to share their views.

Our environment laws are broken. We have to rewrite them so they better protect the environment.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: Teachers are the best. Happy World Teachers’ Day
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
A welcome announcement from @PennySharpemlc 

I love horses, but they don't belong in national parks. Feral horses are causing serious damage to our native plants and animals. Reducing feral horse numbers will protect more than 30 of our precious native threatened species that call the Alps home.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
Images of the Menindee fish kills earlier this year shocked the nation. They reminded us that our native fish and waterways are under threat.

Yesterday I met with locals who had seen the kills first hand.

We are determined to deliver the Murray-Darling Basin Plan to make sure we have a healthy river for communities like this.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
38 years ago today the Hawke Labor Government handed Uluru back to its traditional owners, the Anangu people.

Thanks to decades of struggles and activism, this special part of Australia is now jointly managed by the local community and Parks Australia - ensuring Traditional Owners can care for the land they have been custodians of for generations.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: Chatting with the local @abcnews about this beautiful and historic building.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: We’re nominating Broken Hill and Victorian Trades Halls as part of an international bid to recognise workers’ history on the World Heritage List.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: Starting the day on air with Andrew at @abcnews Broken Hill chatting heritage, water and the Murray-Darling Basin Plan.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
Bill Hayden was smart, loyal, principled and wise. 

He was passionate about the Labor party and determined to make Australia a fairer place. Labor leader. Treasurer. Minister for Foreign Affairs. Governor General. Architect of Medibank. Author of the single mother pension. An advocate for equality and LGBTIQA rights.

Our country has lost a giant. He will be missed.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
We’ve just approved another solar farm - the third renewables project we’ve ticked off on this month.

We’re rebuilding our entire energy system to make Australia a renewable energy superpower.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
Thought I’d give Peter Dutton a reminder about what action looks like. 

We know we need concrete action to end violence against women and children. That’s why we’re investing more than $260 million in First Nations women and children’s safety.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: Thanks for having me.

biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
In case you missed the news, yesterday our legislation to rescue the Murray-Darling Basin Plan passed the House. 

We’re supporting a river system that covers a million square kilometres and provides drinking water for 3 million Australians.

It’s critical we do this now.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
Our water legislation passed the House yesterday. This means we're one step closer to rescuing the Murray-Darling Basin Plan. 

Thanks for chatting with me about it @PatsKarvelas
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: Libs and Nats still asking #qt questions about the Voice - that’s 93 questions on the Voice, but none on education, none on skills and TAFE, none on manufacturing this term. But they say the govt is distracted by the Voice. Hmmmm.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: In #qt the Libs and Nats ask question after question about Voice and now treaty. Last week they called it a distraction and divisive. This week they can’t ask a question about the economy, health, education.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
Today's vote is an important sign of progress for the #MurrayDarling.

Before it passes the Senate, we need to see improvements that deliver First Nations water rights, and guarantees real water will be returned to rivers, now. After a decade of delays, action is well overdue!
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
An update from Parliament: Our Restoring our Rivers Bill has just passed through the House.

This means we are one step closer to getting the Murray-Darling Basin Plan back on track.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: Right now the parliament is debating our legislation to rescue the Murray-Darling Basin Plan. Here’s why that matters.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
Can you believe I spotted all these birds just outside Parliament House. 

It’s bird week and I joined the Aussie Bird count happening all across Australia. Each bird counted on the app will help scientists better understand the condition of our beautiful native birds.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
We’ve ticked off on this solar farm in NSW that will power 56,000 homes. Plus, it won’t disrupt the farming activities on the land.

Another project to help us get us to 82 per cent renewables by 2030.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
Today is sad for many, particularly for First Nations Australians. 

This isn’t the result we wanted. But it is not the end. 

Now, we must redouble our efforts to tackle inequality and give Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander kids a better future. That’s something I believe we can all get behind.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
It’s been a big campaign powered by passion and people coming together to make change. 

Thank you.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: Proud to have voted Yes.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
There is no place for hate. There is no place for offensive slurs and symbols.

Reports of an incident in Darlinghurst today are deeply disturbing.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
Only one day to go. People from all sides of politics are saying Yes. 

Yes to recognition. Yes to reconciliation. Yes to listening. Yes to justice. Yes to better results. 

Thank you @BridgetArcherMP. Thank you Launceston.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
Three days to go. Campaigning with this fantastic crew in Melbourne yesterday.

@JessWalshVic
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: Welcome home Cheng Lei.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
We’ve just added Victorian Trades Hall to the National Heritage list - to recognise and protect this important piece of history. 

Plus, we’re supporting its nomination for World Heritage.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description: Look after yourself and remember you are not defined by this. Good luck.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
We've just approved a massive renewable energy hub in Victoria that will power over 1 million homes.

This is what action on climate change looks like - cutting emissions, more renewables, and protecting our environment.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
My interview on Sunrise yesterday morning: the attacks on Israeli citizens were horrific.

"What we can do is say - unequivocally, join our voices to the voices of other countries saying that these attacks on civilians must stop, the bombing must stop, the taking of hostages, and there is no excuse."
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
Our government is building a circular economy where we produce less and reuse more.                                   

Today, Treasurer @JEChalmers joined me to speak with our Circular Economy Ministerial Advisory Group about how this is part of our government’s push to build a more sustainable economy and reach net zero.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.

name: Tanya Plibersek
description:
Eleven years ago, @JuliaGillard stood in parliament and said enough is enough.

What the speech reminded us was that misogyny doesn't burn itself out, it just gets worse. You have to call it out.
biography: Australian Minister for the Environment and Water. Member for Sydney. Authorised T Plibersek, ALP, Redfern.
